# Changelog

All notable changes to the awesome-book-writing-suite will be documented here.

The format follows [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/).

---

## [1.0.0] — 2026-04-15

### Added
- `PROJECT_INSTRUCTIONS.md` — full studio orchestrator for Claude Projects
- 12 skills covering the complete book writing pipeline:
  - `idea-stress-tester` — pre-writing idea validation
  - `voice-calibrator` — author voice fingerprint extraction
  - `book-architect` — book positioning and chapter architecture
  - `narrative-spine-builder` — thesis evolution, flow logic, motifs
  - `research-evidence-builder` — evidence, case studies, counterarguments
  - `chapter-builder` — full chapter drafting from briefs
  - `reader-journey-mapper` — engagement curve and drop-off mapping
  - `red-team-critic` — hostile argument and logic review
  - `beta-reader-simulator` — persona-based reader simulation
  - `editor-sharpener` — prose clarity, flow, and authority polish
  - `book-launch-kit` — complete launch asset generation
  - `content-repurposer` — book-to-platform content engine
- Cross-skill handoff system with clean output passing between stages
- Chapter-level Review & Polish Loop (red-team → beta-read → journey-map → edit)
- Book Project State tracking across sessions
- Pipeline SVG diagram
- MIT License
